18:59.347 --> 19:02.339
J‘ There's no other way

19:02.475 --> 19:05.057
J‘ I can be with you

19:05.186 --> 19:07.142
J‘ If only your folks

19:07.272 --> 19:09.684
J‘ Would approve

19:09.816 --> 19:12.148
J‘ Seeing like this

19:12.277 --> 19:14.768
J‘ We wouldn't have to do

19:14.904 --> 19:17.691
J‘ No, no, lwon't tell

19:17.824 --> 19:20.941
J‘ Anybody else

19:21.077 --> 19:22.988
J‘ I'm gonna keep it

19:23.121 --> 19:25.737
J‘ All to myself

19:25.874 --> 19:27.705
J‘ I know it's late

19:27.834 --> 19:31.952
J‘ And now I can't wait,
let's steal away...

19:32.088 --> 19:34.044
(Man) Say, brah.

19:36.092 --> 19:37.878
Brah.

19:39.512 --> 19:41.673
Yo, brah!

19:42.932 --> 19:45.184
| just was gonna ask
where my change at.

19:52.817 --> 19:54.978
(Groaning)

20:05.830 --> 20:08.242
— Are you OK?
— You're in charge.

20:08.375 --> 20:11.412
Do what you need to do.
Close up as best you can.

20:11.544 --> 20:13.535
(Car lock chirps)

20:32.607 --> 20:35.974
(Dispatcher) 8-01.
(Man on radio) You just had a call for me?

20:36.111 --> 20:38.397
(Dispatcher) Disregard it.

20:38.530 --> 20:40.521
(Radio chatter continues)

20:49.082 --> 20:51.368
Lieutenant, sign here.

21:05.265 --> 21:07.551
(Camera shutter clicking)

21:30.457 --> 21:33.449
(Man) Things can't be that quiet
in the French Quarter.

21:36.379 --> 21:39.462
Bad one here — a heater.

21:39.591 --> 21:41.582
I heard.

21:41.718 --> 21:44.835
I came past to see
if you guys need manpower.

21:44.971 --> 21:47.337
I can spare a couple guys
for your canvass.

21:47.474 --> 21:49.760
No, we're good.

21:49.893 --> 21:52.509
