so not much blood.

22:01.279 --> 22:04.146
Uh-huh.
And the husband?

22:04.282 --> 22:07.194
He's asleep in the bed with the son?

22:07.327 --> 22:08.692
So he says.

22:08.828 --> 22:10.739
One shot, grazes him in the cheek.

22:10.872 --> 22:13.113
Says he gets up,
he runs to the bathroom.

22:13.249 --> 22:15.956
Two more shots -
the forearm and the hand.

22:16.085 --> 22:18.701
Still he looks good, the kid too.

22:18.838 --> 22:20.294
Looks like a straight—up robbery.

22:20.423 --> 22:22.163
But, Terry, the way this guy played it...

22:22.300 --> 22:24.916
The guy's shot three times.
He's in the fucking hospital, right?

22:25.053 --> 22:26.839
You didn't see how he reacted
to his wife's death.

22:26.971 --> 22:29.178
The guy's in shock.
I fucking would be.

22:29.307 --> 22:31.218
I got a feeling about this.

22:35.813 --> 22:38.600
(Grunts) Wow,

22:39.359 --> 22:41.816
— you're up early.
— Mm—hm.

22:41.945 --> 22:43.856
Today | write a song.

22:43.988 --> 22:45.774
What?

22:46.574 --> 22:48.314
Really? Can I help?

22:48.451 --> 22:52.785
Oh, I'm not sure you should.
I think it has to be my song.

22:58.253 --> 23:01.245
So what are you gonna start with,

23:01.381 --> 23:04.839
- the melody or the lyrics?
— Which do you start with?

23:04.968 --> 23:07.755
— Lyrics.
— Oh, well, melody for me, then.

23:09.055 --> 23:10.841
(Laughs)

23:10.974 --> 23:14.182
- Where are you going?
— I got a business meeting.

23:16.646 --> 23:19.103
Dressed like that?

23:19.232 --> 23:21.689
It's the music business.

23:23.861 --> 23:25.692
(Man over radio) 8—41.

23:27.240 --> 23:29.777
(Dispatcher) Go ahead, 8—41.

23:29.909 --> 23:33.993
